# Template only: copy to `.env.local` (recommended) or `.env` in this folder.
# Real env files are gitignored. Vite exposes only variables prefixed with VITE_ to client code — treat them as public.

# Optional default API origin (no path suffix, no trailing slash). Not a secret; browsers can see this URL anyway.
#
# Most users set their server URL in the app at Register (stored in localStorage). Sign in reuses that URL;
# expand "Use a different server" on the login form only when you need to change it. You only need VITE_API_URL
# when you want to pre-fill the Register field — for example local dev pointing at http://localhost:8080
# without typing it each time.
#
# Resolution order at runtime: user-configured URL in the app → VITE_API_URL (if set) → http://localhost:8080
#
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8080
